data.name: Calculate Income Taxes
filing_status
data.description: The filing status (either "single", "married", "married_separately", or "head_of_household").

data.name: pay_periods
data.description: The number of pay periods in a year.  If not passed, this will default to 1, Taxee will assume the pay_rate value is an annual income, and the results will be amounts owed for an entire year. If a value is passed, the results will be amounts owed per pay period.

data.name: pay_rate
data.description: The individual or household income of the person or family.

data.name: state
data.description: The filer's state abbreviation.  If no state is provided, the state income tax amount will not be returned.

data.name: year
data.description: The year of the federal income tax information you'd like to request.
Given a year, returns tax brackets and deductions for all filing statuses.
